defaultof relevance
default to the microbiological 
defaultside
default; BBSRC funding
default for ‘industrial biotechnology and bioenergy’ amounts to 
default£26.2
defaultm in 2012/13, but this is split between 18 often eclectic areas ranging from tissue engineering to biomass crops.
default The 
defaultfocus
default 
defaultis therefore
default diffuse
default,
default with 
defaultrelatively little opportunity for 
defaultthe 
defaultscientific
default 
defaultcommittees
default that allocate
default research
default 
defaultfunds
default to ma
defaultke 
defaultmajor investment in one area.
default&#xa0;
defaultThere is, as a consequence, a huge funding gap for applied microbiological research in technology readiness levels 1-4 (discovery, research
default,
default and proof of concept)
default for key areas of
default basic science underlying
default industrial biotechno
defaultlogy
default.
default 
default 
